annotationA: Syntaxin 16; SNAP receptor activity; protein binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: vesicle-mediated transport; synaptic vesicle docking involved in exocytosis; Golgi vesicle transport; intracellular protein transport; neurotransmitter secretion; Belongs to the syntaxin family
annotationB: Golgi SNAP receptor complex member 1; Involved in transport from the ER to the Golgi apparatus as well as in intra-Golgi transport. It belongs to a super-family of proteins called t-SNAREs or soluble NSF (N-ethylmaleimide- sensitive factor) attachment protein receptor (By similarity)
